                                        <depth unit="cm">7.5</depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </support>
                                <condition/>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout>
                                    <p>Three lines of Latin text, centred on stone. Interpuncts are all slightly different from each other, but shaped (roughly) like horizontal commas, and notably placed at line beginnings and ends as well as between words. Although Bivona (1994) claims that there are traces of guidelines, these are not visible upon autopsy.</p>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</rs>
                                    <damage/>
                                </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote>
                                <p>Most letters have a broad fairly square module and are regular, with simple straight line serifs. Text is rendered in straight lines. Incision of letters is not particularly deep.</p>
