            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Herennia Polla, daughter of Gaius. Farewell!</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#AA">
                <p>Polla, here a cognomen, is derived from a common praenomen for women. For the gens Herennia, see also L. Herennius Certus, also attested at Thermae Himeraeae, <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000181">ISic000181</ref>, as well as elsewhere in Sicily, e.g. <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000496">iSic000496</ref> and <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000561">ISic00561</ref>. The gens Herennia is exceptionally well attested in republican literature and coinage, see Bivona (1994, 200).</p>
            </div>
